PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1773857158
OL,3,CScotland's decision on assisted dying
OL,4,Ctakes pressure off England and Wales
OL,6,FNow, opponents in the House of Lords
OL,7,Fwill no doubt argue that objecting to
OL,8,Fthe bill isn't filibustering or
OL,9,Fconstitutional game-playing ` as
OL,10,Fthey've always insisted it isn't. It
OL,11,Fis principled opposition, in their
OL,12,Fview, to a flawed bill, which has many
OL,13,Fsimilarities to Scotland's.
OL,15,FPointing to Holyrood, they can argue
OL,16,Fthat MSPs have reached the same
OL,17,Fconclusion about the risks and dangers
OL,18,Fof assisted dying.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
